ball Championship|2013 Canada]] | }}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2011 Men's NORCECA Volleyball Championship|2011 Puerto Rico]] | }}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2009 Men's NORCECA Volleyball Championship|2009 Puerto Rico]] | }}\n}}\n\n'''Paul Michael Lotman''' (born 3 November 1985) is an [[United States|American]] [[volleyball player]], a member of the [[United States men's national volleyball team]] and [[India|Indian]] club [[Calicut Heroes]], a participant of the [[Olympic Games]] [[2012 Summer Olympics|London 2012]], [[2013 Men's NORCECA Volleyball Championship|NORCECA Champion 2013]], gold medalist of the [[2008 Men's Pan-American Volleyball Cup|2008 Pan American Cup]], [[2014 FIVB Volleyball World League|2014 World League]] and [[2015 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|2015 World Cup]], three\u2013time [[PlusLiga|Polish Champion]] ([[2011\u201312 PlusLiga|2012]], [[2012\u201313 PlusLiga|2013]], [[2014\u201315 PlusLiga|2015]]), [[Deutsche Volleyball-Bundesliga|German Champion]] (2016).\n\n==Personal life==\nLotman was born in [[Lakewood, California]]. His parents are Kathleen and Albert Lotman (his father died in 2011). He has two older brothers, Mark and Steven, and an older sister Shelley. He attended Los Alamitos High School (1999\u20132003). He graduated from [[California State University, Long Beach]] (better known as Long Beach State) in 2008 with a degree in sociology. On August 2011 he married Jasmine.<ref>[http://www.volleywood.net/usav-volleyball-news/lotmans-wedding-pics/ ''Lotman\u2019s Wedding Pics''] \u2013 volleywood.net \u2013 2011-08-23</ref> On December 20, 2016 his wife gave birth to their son Leif Albert Lotman.\n\n[[File:Paul Lotman.jpg|thumb|Lotman before match Piacenza \u2013 Verona on January 27, 2011.]]\n\n==Career==\n\n===Clubs===\nIn 2011 he joined the Polish club [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]].<ref>[http://volley24.pl/index.php/rozgrywki-mezczyzn/plusliga/14922-paul-lotman-kolejnym-przyjmujcym-w-rzeszowie ''Paul Lotman kolejnym przyjmuj\u0105cym w Rzeszowie''] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20140404162513/http://volley24.pl/index.php/rozgrywki-mezczyzn/plusliga/14922-paul-lotman-kolejnym-przyjmujcym-w-rzeszowie |date=April 4, 2014 }} \u2013 volley24.pl \u2013 2011-05-18</ref> With the club from [[Rzesz\u00f3w]] he won three titles of [[PlusLiga|Polish Champion]] ([[2011\u201312 PlusLiga|2012]], [[2012\u201313 PlusLiga|2013]], [[2014\u201315 PlusLiga|2015]]), Polish SuperCup and the silver medal of [[2011\u201312 Men's CEV Cup|CEV Cup]] 2012. On March 29, 2015 [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]], including Lotman, achieved silver medal of the [[2014\u201315 CEV Champions League]].<ref>[http://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/CompetitionNews.aspx?ID=736&NewsID=19956&TagType=0&TagContent=0&NewsType=0&Paging=0&Sd=1/1/1900&Ed=1/1/1900 ''Three is the magic number for Russian armada from Tatarstan!''] \u2013 cev.eu \u2013 2015-03-29</ref> He left [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w|Asseco Resovia]] in May 2015. In June 2015 he moved to German team [[Berlin Recycling Volleys]].<ref>[http://eurosport.onet.pl/siatkowka/plus-liga/paul-lotman-siatkarzem-berlin-recycling-volleys/e7tcyl ''Paul Lotman siatkarzem Berlin Recycling Volleys''] \u2013 onet.pl \u2013 2015-06-18</ref> In 2017 he moved to Indonesian volleyball club [[Jakarta BNI Taplus]] for 2017/2018 season.\n\n===National team===\nLotman made his [[Olympic games|Olympic]] debut with the [[United States men's national volleyball team|U.S. national team]] in [[2012 Olympics]] in London.\n\n===Coaching===\nIn 2019, Lotman began working as a volunteer assistant coach with the [[UC San Diego]] Tritons men's volleyball team.\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''[[CEV Champions League]]'''\n** [[File:Silver medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2014\u201315 CEV Champions League|2014/2015]] \u2013 with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n\n* '''[[CEV Cup]]'''\n** [[File:Simple silver cup.svg|16px]] [[2011\u201312 Men's CEV Cup|2011/2012]] \u2013 with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n** [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2015\u201316 Men's CEV Cup|2015/2016]] \u2013 with [[Berlin Recycling Volleys]]\n\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''2007/2008''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Puerto Rican Championship, with [[Plataneros de Corozal]]\n** '''2011/2012''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2011\u201312 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n** '''2012/2013''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2012\u201313 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n** '''2013/2014''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish SuperCup, with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n** '''2013/2014''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2013\u201314 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n** '''2014/2015''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2014\u201315 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n** '''2015/2016''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] German Cup, with [[Berlin Recycling Volleys]]\n** '''2015/2016''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Deutsche Volleyball-Bundesliga|German Championship]], with [[Berlin Recycling Volleys]]\n** '''2018/2019''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Pro Volleyball League|Indian Championship]], with [[Calicut Heroes]]\n\n* '''National team'''\n** '''2008''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2008 Men's Pan-American Volleyball Cup|Pan-American Cup]]\n** '''2009''' [[File:Silver medal northamerica.svg|16px]] [[2009 Men's NORCECA Volleyball Championship|NORCECA Championship]]\n** '''2011''' [[File:Silver medal northamerica.svg|16px]] [[2011 Men's NORCECA Volleyball Championship|NORCECA Championship]]\n** '''2013''' [[File:Gold medal northamerica.svg|16px]] [[2013 Men's NORCECA Volleyball Championship|NORCECA Championship]]\n** '''2014''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2014 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]]\n** '''2015''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2015 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]]\n** '''2015''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2015 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|FIVB World Cup]]\n\n===Individually===\n* '''2016:''' [[2015\u201316 Men's CEV Cup|CEV Cup]] \u2013 Most Valuable Player\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons}}\n* [http://www.teamusa.org/Athletes/LO/Paul-Lotman Team USA player profile]\n* [https://www.plusliga.pl/players/id/419.html PlusLiga player profile]\n* [https://www.instagram.com/paullotman/ Instagram player profile]\n\n{{United States men's volleyball squad 2012 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Footer USA Volleyball 2012 Summer Olympics}}\n{{United States men volleyball team 2015 FIVB World Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lotman, Paul}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Lakewood, California]]\n[[Category:American men's volleyball players]]\n[[Category:Olympic volleyball players of the United States]]\n[[Category:Volleyball players at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Polish Champions of men's volleyball]]\n[[Category:Long Beach State Beach men's volleyball players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Poland]]\n[[Category:Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w players]]\n[[Category:PAOK V.C. players]]\n", "name_user": "Zyxw", "label": "safe", "comment": "use template for USOPC link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul_Lotman"}
